JOHANNESBURG – Telkom has terminated the appointment of Nkonki Inc as its joint external auditors. This follows the disgraced firm’s decision to file for voluntary liquidation. READ: Telkom cautions shareholders The partially state-owned telecommunications company announced in August last year it was in the process of procuring the firm for its external audit services. EY will remain the sole auditors for Telkom’s Annual Financial Statements for the year ended in March 2018. Shareholders have been told PriceWaterhouseCoopers and Sizwe-Ntsaluba-Gobodo will be nominated jointly at the company’s next AGM in August this year. eNCA